    Weapon And Armor Proficiency::text
      A fighter/sorcerer is proficient with all simple and martial weapons and with all armor (heavy, medium, and light) and shields (including tower shields). A fighter/sorcerer cannot cast any spells while wearing armor. 
    
      At 1st level, a fighter/sorcerer can choose to instead be able to cast spells in armor. If he does, use the armored fighter/sorcerer spell table instead.

    Bonus Fighter Feat::text
      At 1st level and every even level, the fighter/sorcerer gets a bonus fighter feat.

    Spells::text
      The fighter/sorcerer casts, and learns spells in the same manner a sorcerer does. See the sorcerer for full information. However use the Fighter/Sorcerer spells per long rest table (or the armored fighter/sorcerer spells per long rest table). He uses the sorcerer spells known table.

    Bonus Sorcerer Feat::text
      At 5th level, the fighter/sorcerer gets a bonus sorcerer feat.
